Load Excel File Into Power Bi Desktop 7

Step 1: Load Data into Power Bi Desktop

1.    Download the DUI_Fatalities excel file from the Red Icon  and save the DUI_Fatalities file in your computer.

2.    Open Power Bi Desktop, from the Home tab and click on Get Data

3.    Select the excel from the options.

4.    Upload the DUI_Fatalities excel file from your computer

5.    Select the file (DUI_Fatalities and US_Holiday_Date ) from the Power Bi desktop Display Options

6.    Click on Load button to load the data into power BI Desktop


 Follow the gif below to load data into the power Bi Desktop 



To learn more about how to load an excel workbook into Power BI, click the link below:
